Wealth Management
What we offer
Investing your wealth
Investment products




Investment products

Our investment products range from traditional equity and bond funds to hedge funds and commercial real estate – all handpicked by experts. All investments can fall in value as well as rise, so you might not get back what you originally invested.








At Barclays we see investments as part of your overall wealth plan. We’ll work with you to develop the right portfolio for your goals and give you an unparalleled insight into how your money is performing.










Traditional funds     

Invest in cash, bonds, equities and more

Diverse funds managed by experts form an excellent base for your portfolio.

Investment management handled by leading fund managers
A simple, flexible way to diversify
Funds to suit almost every goal
Short, medium and long term investments (though bond and equity funds are best held for at least five years)






Barclays MultiManager     

Gain access to some of the world's finest investment managers in a single fund.

Diversify and spread risk by using investment managers with different styles and talents.

Smoother returns 
Efficient investment strategies
A risk profile to suit your strategy
Available in sterling, euro and US dollar






GlobalAccess     

Offering a range of equity and fixed income funds utilising the skills of world-leading investment managers

Choose one or more single asset or investment funds to build a specialist tailored portfolio.

Access to world-leading investment managers, some of which are not normally available to individual investors
Managed by a team of in-house investment professionals
Wide range of specialist equity and fixed income funds
Available in sterling, euro and US dollar






Barclays GlobalBeta     

A portfolio of globally diversified index funds  

Tracks the market for more consistent, reliable returns while keeping your costs low.

Broad diversification aiming for smoother investment returns
A diverse, transparent portfolio
Lower costs, less paperwork
Managed by experts
Available in sterling, euro and dollar






Structured products     

Allows you to take exposure to an underlying investment of your choice, in accordance with your investment objectives and your risk tolerance.

Different structured products will offer different degrees of exposure to the performance of an underlying asset, with diverse ways of providing upside or income and controlling downside exposure:


Upside exposure: Enhanced market participation, digital payoff, yield enhancement
Downside exposure: Full, conditional, or partial repayment of capital at maturity or full risk to capital



Through structured products, you can access a wide range of assets. Our expertise covers equities, interest rates, currencies, commodities and real estate. Structured products can provide enhanced return or income and increased diversification for your portfolios.


You can get access to a wide range of assets, including equities, commodities, real estate and FX.
Our access to more than 15 counterparties enables us to deliver value for you on a consistent basis in terms of pricing. competitiveness, quality of service and innovation.
Market leading team of industry experts design the products  Post-sale support is a valuable part of our service, and we monitor our products accordingly.
The potential return on structured products and any repayment of capital is usually linked to an index or other asset’s performance during a term of, typically, 3 to 5 years. If the index does well you might get your money back and a return; if not you might get no return and less than you invested by way of capital repayment at the end.
Structured products are issued by financial institutions and are dependent on those institutions to meet their liabilities.
You can sell structured products before the end of their term but might get back less than you invested.











