Company Overview of The Investment House Funds - The Investment House Growth Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Investment House Funds - The Investment House Growth Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by The Investment House, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in growth oriented stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. It employs fundamental analysis by focusing on factors such as strong earnings growth, reasonable valuations, quality management, financial strength and stability, and economic cycle to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index. It was formerl...
The Investment House Funds - The Investment House Growth Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by The Investment House, LLC. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in growth oriented stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. It employs fundamental analysis by focusing on factors such as strong earnings growth, reasonable valuations, quality management, financial strength and stability, and economic cycle to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index. It was formerly known as The GKM Funds - GKM Growth Fund. The Investment House Funds - The Investment House Growth Fund was formed on December 28, 2001 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


